{"title":"The New Wilde Waypoint Carbon Fork is Full-Featured and Lightweight","link":"https://bikerumor.com/wilde-waypoint-carbon-fork-dyanmo-fender-mounts/","date":1709567932000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero.jpeg\" alt=\"Wilde Bicycle Co. Waypoint Carbon Fork hero\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Wilde Bicycle Co. takes pride in being a small company that likes to help small companies. A small bike company out of Minneapolis, MN, today they are introducing a new <a href=\"https://www.wildebikes.com/collections/frontpage/products/waypoint-carbon-fork-tapered\" target=\"_blank\">lightweight carbon fork</a>. Their new Waypoint Tapered Carbon Gravel fork weighs in at 478g and “is among the lightest fully featured carbon forks on the market.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-in-the-weeds-e1709355386436.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"755\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-in-the-weeds-e1709355386436.jpeg\" alt=\"Wilde Bicycle Co. Waypoint Carbon Fork in the weeds\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-in-the-weeds-e1709355386436.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-in-the-weeds-e1709355386436-297x175.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-in-the-weeds-e1709355386436-800x472.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-in-the-weeds-e1709355386436-120x71.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-in-the-weeds-e1709355386436-768x453.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Wilde Bicycle Co.)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Jeff Frane, President of Wilde Bicycle Co., says that he’s “<em>Most excited about the ability to serve other small frame builders by providing them with killer OEM pricing if they want to use it or the Wayfinder (our straight steerer carbon fork) on their builds</em>.”  </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Wilde Waypoint Carbon Fork</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Wilde thought the existing offerings in the carbon gravel fork category seemed too stiff and heavy for their liking. Wilde’s <a href=\"https://www.wildebikes.com/collections/bikes/products/earth-ship-steel-frameset\" target=\"_blank\">Earth Ship</a>‘s lightweight and supple feel is where that bike shines. With that in mind, they ventured to design a fork from the ground up. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In comes the Waypoint. With an uncut steerer, the Waypoint weighs in at 478g. As mentioned earlier Wilde thinks that it’s among the lightest full-featured forks on the market. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-adventure-nips.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-adventure-nips.jpeg\" alt=\"Wilde Bicycle Co. Waypoint Carbon Fork adventure nips\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-adventure-nips.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-adventure-nips-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-adventure-nips-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-adventure-nips-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-adventure-nips-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-adventure-nips-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Wilde Bicycle Co.)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The fork legs were specifically designed to soak up the rough stuff and isolate the rider from any road chatter. thus, allowing the rider to perform longer and in greater comfiness. The fork is said to accomplish this task without sacrificing strength or durability. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Ready for Adventure</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-cable-routing.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-cable-routing.jpeg\" alt=\"Wilde Bicycle Co. Waypoint Carbon Fork internal cable routing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-cable-routing.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-cable-routing-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-cable-routing-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-cable-routing-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-cable-routing-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-cable-routing-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Internal brake cable routing</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-dynamo-routing.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-dynamo-routing.jpeg\" alt=\"Wilde Bicycle Co. Waypoint Carbon Fork internal dynamo routing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-dynamo-routing.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-dynamo-routing-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-dynamo-routing-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-dynamo-routing-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-dynamo-routing-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-internal-dynamo-routing-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Internal dynamo light routing</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-logo.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-logo.jpeg\" alt=\"Wilde Bicycle Co. Waypoint Carbon Fork logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-logo.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-logo-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-logo-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-logo-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-logo-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-logo-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Three-pack mounts</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Waypoint looks to have all of the features you would need for doing some exploring, some gravel grinding, or bikepacking. It has three-pack mounts, internal dynamo routing (<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-sinewave-beacon-2-dynamo-bicycle-light/\" target=\"_blank\">yes!</a>), internal cable routing, fender mounts (with a fully threaded center mount), and great tire clearance. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-thru-axle.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-thru-axle.jpeg\" alt=\"Wilde Bicycle Co. Waypoint Carbon Fork thru axle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-thru-axle.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-thru-axle-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-thru-axle-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-thru-axle-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-thru-axle-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-thru-axle-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Waypoint was designed for bikes with an EC34/44 or straight 44mm headtube that takes a tapered steerer. If you need a fork for a standard straight 1-1/8″ steerer or EC34 headtube, the OG <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wilde-bikes-wayfinder-straight-1-1-8-steerer-modern-gravel-fork-dynamo-routing/\" target=\"_blank\">Wayfinder</a> would be your jam. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the Wayfinder, the new Waypoint would be a great solution for adding features and lightening up bikes like the All-City Cosmic Stallion, Surly Midnight Special, etc. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-big-tire-clearance.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-big-tire-clearance.jpeg\" alt=\"Wilde Bicycle Co. Waypoint Carbon Fork big tire clearance\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-big-tire-clearance.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-big-tire-clearance-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-big-tire-clearance-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-big-tire-clearance-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-big-tire-clearance-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-big-tire-clearance-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Big tire clearance</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Wilde wants you to know that if you are a frame builder, they are offering terrific OEM pricing options and would love to work with you. Just shoot them an <a href=\"wildebikes@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">email</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero2.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero2.jpeg\" alt=\"Wilde Bicycle Co. Waypoint Carbon Fork hero2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero2.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero2-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero2-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero2-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero2-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wilde-Bicycle-Co.-Waypoint-Carbon-Fork-hero2-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Waypoint Retail, Features, and Specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $525</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Three Pack Mounts</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Flat Mount Brake</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Thru Axle – 12x100mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Internal Brake Routing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Internal Dynamo Routing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fender Mounts</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fully Threaded Center Mount</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Fork Weight: 478g with uncut steerer</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tire Clearance: 700c X 2.1″ or 27.5″ X 2.3″</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Axle to Crown: 398mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rake: 49mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Steerer: 350mm length, Taper 1.125″ to 1.5″</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Spacing: 100mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Axle Length: 130mm 12 x 1.5</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Compatible Rotor Size: 140mm and 160mm</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Capacity:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>ThreePack Mount: 6lbs per side</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rack: 20lbs</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.wildebikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">WildeBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wilde-waypoint-carbon-fork-dyanmo-fender-mounts/\">The New Wilde Waypoint Carbon Fork is Full-Featured and Lightweight</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"acf3d32a3a93554f6e8846e1ef4c4aa7fcd9a8471a6edcf4fef2509cc5d825a7","category":"Cycling"}